{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φέγγος</b>, εος, τό, <br /> <b>light, splendour, lustre,</b> τῆλε δὲ φ. ἀπὸ χροὸς ἀθανάτοιο λάμπε θεᾶς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Cererem” 278; τὸ φ. τῆς χρόας 4th-3rd c.BC: Duris Epigrammaticus 14 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus; τὸ φ. τῆς δόξης Κυρίου LXX.Eze.10.4 \">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>]; φ. ἀστραπῆς ὅπλων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.Hab.3.11 \">LXX</a>]: frequently like{φάος}, of <b>daylight,</b> either <i>absolutely</i> or with some word added, φ. ἡλίου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 377, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 606, etc.; τὸ φ. τοῦ θεοῦ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 722 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; without the <i>Article</i>, φ. εἰσορᾶν θεοῦ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Or.” 1025, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 673 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὦ φέγγος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 859, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 866; ὦ φ. ἡμέρας 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1577; δεκάτῳ φέγγει ἔτους in the tenth year, [prev. work] 504. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> <b>moonlight,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cynegeticus” 5.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; νυκτερινὰ φέγγη, opposed to ἡμερινὸν φῶς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 508c; ἐὰν τὸ φ. ἐκλείψῃ “Catalogus Codicum Astrologorum” 4.172, compare 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 38.255; φῶς ἡμέρας, φέγγος σελήνης 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] see at {φέγγο; τὸ φ. [τοῦ γάλακτος}], of the milky way, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 346a26. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__c</b></Level4> of men, φ. ἰδεῖν, προσιδεῖν, to see <b>the light,</b> come into the world, ἐπεὶ πάμπρωτον εἶδον φ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.111; ἀελίου προσιδεῖν φ. 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 5.162; λιπεῖν φ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 954; ὄλωλα, φ. οὐκέτ᾽ ἔστι μοι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1144. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__d</b></Level4> <b>day,</b> τριταῖον ἤδη φ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 32, compare 2nd c.BC: Sosiphanes Tragicus 3.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μοιρίδιον φ. ={μ. ἦμαρ}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Eleg.” 2. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>the light</b> of torches or fire, φ. λαμπάδων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 1022 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; πυρός[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 1029, “Ch.” 1037 \">Refs</a>]: <b>a light, torch,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 448, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 1.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>plural</i> φέγγη <b>torches</b> or <b>watch-fires,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeneas Tacticus 10.26 (conjecture), 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Camillus” 25, etc. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>the light</b> of the eyes, φ. ὀμμάτων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 368, 1035; ὄσσων 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 24.75 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τυφλὸν φ, i.e. blindness, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 1068 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>light,</b> as a <i>metaphorically</i> for delight, glory, pride, joy, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 8.97, “N.” 3.64, 4.13; τί γὰρ γυναικὶ τούτου φ. ἥδιον δρακεῖν, ἀπὸ στρατείας ἀνδρὶ σώσαντος θεοῦ πύλας ἀνοῖξα; 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 602 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of persons, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 9.42; μέγα βροτοῖσι φ. Ἀσκληπιόν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 640 (Lyric poetry); Μουσέων φ. Ὅμηρον “Anthologia Graeca” 7.6 (Antip. Sid.); ὦ ταῖς ἱεραῖς φ. Ἀθήναις 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1319 (_anapaest meter_); πλοῦτος.. ἀνδρὶ φ. 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 2.56 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φ. ὀπώρας, of wine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “fragment” 153. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>lustre,</b> δικαιοσύνης καὶ σωφροσύνης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 250b; φ. ἐλέους LXX.3Mac.6.4; τῆς ψυχῆς τὸ γάνωμα καὶ τὸ φ. 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.792a, etc. \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5338","accentedUnicode":"φέγγος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5457","matchingForm":"φῶς","stepTransliteration":"fōs","gloss":"light","_zh_tw_Gloss":"光","_es_Gloss":"luz","_zh_Gloss":"光"}],"shortDef":"light, radiance","mediumDef":"light, radiance <br /><b>light, splendor, radiance,</b> <ref='Mat.24.29'>Mt. 24:29</ref>; <ref='Mrk.13.24'>Mk. 13:24</ref>*","stepGloss":"brightness","stepTransliteration":"fengos","count":2,"_es_Definition":"luz","_zh_tw_Definition":"光, 光芒","_zh_Definition":"光, 光芒","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự toả sáng.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"光","_es_Gloss":"luz","_zh_Gloss":"光"}]}